22/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Representatives of Macedonia's ruling party, the Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia, and the largest opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE, met on Tuesday (21 October) to discuss the preparation of a common Euro-Atlantic Strategy, which would serve as a guideline for successive governments.
The meeting was initiated by VMRO-DPMNE and indicated a warming in relations after months of tension.
The talks focused on a document of national consensus and the timetable for submission of Macedonia's official application for EU membership candidate status.
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 22/10/03)
